summary:
The Security Council:

Recalling its relevant resolutions on Iraq, notes the Final Report of the Governing Council of the United Nations Compensation Commission (the Commission) and the United Nations Compensation Fund (the Fund).

The Council:

1. Decides the Commission has fulfilled its mandate under resolutions 687 (1991) and 692 (1991);
2. Reaffirms Iraq has fulfilled its international obligations to compensate claimants for losses from its invasion of Kuwait;
3. Confirms Iraq no longer needs to deposit a percentage of petroleum and natural gas proceeds into the Fund;
4. Confirms the Commission's claims process is complete and final, with no further claims allowed;
5. Encourages recipients of environmental remediation awards to continue projects and inform Iraq of progress;
6. Requests the UN Secretariat to provide Iraq access to Commission claims records;
7. Decides to terminate the Commission's mandate, concluding outstanding matters by the end of 2022, and return remaining Fund amounts to Iraq;
8. Decides to conclude its consideration of Commission compensation and close the Commission and dissolve the Fund upon completion.
